1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:05,040
Attention, Albert Hall, London, UK,
Planet Earth!

2
00:00:05,040 --> 00:00:09,960
I am the Vlinkstatic
X-Form Robo-Neuro-Actoform

3
00:00:09,960 --> 00:00:15,920
Designation Number 5576, but you can
call me "The Vlinx!"

4
00:00:15,920 --> 00:00:18,200
Hello!
AUDIENCE: Hello!

5
00:00:18,200 --> 00:00:20,640
I said, "Hello"!

6
00:00:20,640 --> 00:00:22,840
AUDIENCE: HELLO!
Thank you.

7
00:00:22,840 --> 00:00:28,000
And it is my greatest function to
introduce a very special guest -

8
00:00:28,000 --> 00:00:31,800
human beings, please welcome...
The Doctor!

9
00:00:31,800 --> 00:00:33,880
VWORP!

10
00:00:33,880 --> 00:00:36,200
Hello!

11
00:00:33,880 --> 00:00:36,200
AUDIENCE CHEER

12
00:00:36,200 --> 00:00:40,200
Hello, there, Royal Albert Hall.
HE LAUGHS

13
00:00:41,440 --> 00:00:43,160
OK, look at you!

14
00:00:43,160 --> 00:00:45,120
ALARM BLARES

15
00:00:43,160 --> 00:00:45,120
Emergency, emergency!

16
00:00:45,120 --> 00:00:47,720
The Albert Hall is being invaded!

17
00:00:47,720 --> 00:00:50,360
Save yourselves, because here
comes...

18
00:00:50,360 --> 00:00:53,280
MELODIC CACKLING

19
00:00:50,360 --> 00:00:53,280
..The Pantheon of Discord!

20
00:00:53,280 --> 00:00:54,920
SING-SONG: Ta-dah!

21
00:00:54,920 --> 00:00:56,880
AUDIENCE CHEER AND BOO

22
00:00:59,000 --> 00:01:03,800
I am...Maestro, the God of Music,

23
00:01:03,800 --> 00:01:08,880
And music is MINE!

24
00:01:08,880 --> 00:01:10,720
THEY CACKLE,
AUDIENCE CHUCKLE

25
00:01:10,720 --> 00:01:13,840
Oh, scream all you like!

26
00:01:13,840 --> 00:01:16,160
Yeah, yeah, yeah -

27
00:01:16,160 --> 00:01:18,360
you tiny little human pimples!

28
00:01:18,360 --> 00:01:19,600
THEY LAUGH

29
00:01:19,600 --> 00:01:22,960
Cos the Doctor can't stop me this
time!

30
00:01:22,960 --> 00:01:25,560
My powers are vast and godlike,

31
00:01:25,560 --> 00:01:29,480
and my hairstyle is exquisite,
don't you think?

32
00:01:30,720 --> 00:01:37,240
And now, I have an orchestra in the
world's finest auditorium!

33
00:01:37,240 --> 00:01:43,520
And I will feast, because I know
that when humans hear bad music,

34
00:01:43,520 --> 00:01:46,760
it creates a dissonance in your
heads.

35
00:01:46,760 --> 00:01:48,960
AUDIENCE LAUGH

36
00:01:46,760 --> 00:01:48,960
Yeah, dissonance!

37
00:01:48,960 --> 00:01:52,040
Get me and my fancy vocabulary,
chickadees.

38
00:01:52,040 --> 00:01:54,960
Ha! Diss-o-nance!

39
00:01:54,960 --> 00:01:59,360
And that pain becomes food and drink
for me.

40
00:01:59,360 --> 00:02:01,160
Now, you will suffer,

41
00:02:01,160 --> 00:02:06,800
and I will grow in power as I
command this orchestra to play

42
00:02:06,800 --> 00:02:09,720
the world's worst song EVER!

43
00:02:09,720 --> 00:02:11,440
THEY LAUGH

44
00:02:11,440 --> 00:02:14,480
That's right, boys, and girls, and
everyone,

45
00:02:14,480 --> 00:02:19,760
it's your all-time LEAST favourite
song - "I've Got A Dog"!

46
00:02:19,760 --> 00:02:21,840
THEY CACKLE,
CHEERING

47
00:02:21,840 --> 00:02:23,680
And a-one, and a-two...

48
00:02:23,680 --> 00:02:26,320
MUSIC: "I've Got A Dog"
by Murray Gold

49
00:02:26,320 --> 00:02:28,440
Oh... Mmm...

50
00:02:28,440 --> 00:02:30,720
Tasty... More, more!

51
00:02:28,440 --> 00:02:30,720
THEY CACKLE

52
00:02:30,720 --> 00:02:32,880
# I've got a Dog
He's called Fred

53
00:02:32,880 --> 00:02:35,800
# My dog is alive
He's not dead

54
00:02:35,800 --> 00:02:37,160
# I love my dog... #

55
00:02:37,160 --> 00:02:38,400
Tasty!

56
00:02:37,160 --> 00:02:38,400
THEY CACKLE

57
00:02:38,400 --> 00:02:40,800
# He loves me too
I haven't got a cat

58
00:02:40,800 --> 00:02:42,800
# Only a dog
My Dog, my Dog... #

59
00:02:42,800 --> 00:02:43,920
Whoops! Excuse me.

60
00:02:43,920 --> 00:02:45,080
# My Dog, my Dog... #

61
00:02:45,080 --> 00:02:46,880
I am FEASTING, after all! Ha!

62
00:02:46,880 --> 00:02:47,960
# I have a dog
I love my dog... #

63
00:02:47,960 --> 00:02:50,240
Emergency message from the Doctor!

64
00:02:50,240 --> 00:02:54,640
He recommends that everyone starts
clapping - IMMEDIATELY!

65
00:02:54,640 --> 00:02:57,160
Human beings must clap!

66
00:02:57,160 --> 00:03:00,480
CHEERING AND APPLAUSE

67
00:03:02,680 --> 00:03:07,520
But I love the applause - it is
music to my ears.

68
00:03:07,520 --> 00:03:10,000
Everyone SHOULD adore me!

69
00:03:10,000 --> 00:03:13,160
The Doctor has an astute grasp of
logic,

70
00:03:13,160 --> 00:03:18,000
because applause takes place
ONLY when the music has stopped!

71
00:03:18,000 --> 00:03:22,640
Therefore, clapping will cancel out
Maestro's powers.

72
00:03:22,640 --> 00:03:26,200
Recommendation - applause from all.

73
00:03:26,200 --> 00:03:29,440
Don't just clap, stand up, cheer!

74
00:03:29,440 --> 00:03:31,000
No!
CHEERING AND APPLAUSE

75
00:03:31,000 --> 00:03:32,880
Stomp your feet!

76
00:03:32,880 --> 00:03:35,360
Make a lot of noise!

77
00:03:35,360 --> 00:03:38,680
No, no, no! STOP, I beg of you!

78
00:03:38,680 --> 00:03:41,680
Go crazy! No, stop, please!

79
00:03:41,680 --> 00:03:42,960
I'm going to...

80
00:03:43,920 --> 00:03:46,240
..EXPLODE!

81
00:03:46,240 --> 00:03:48,440
CHEERING AND APPLAUSE

82
00:03:54,640 --> 00:03:58,200
Operation Maestro a complete
success!

83
00:03:58,200 --> 00:04:00,400
Congratulations!

84
00:04:00,400 --> 00:04:05,520
And don't forget - Maestro is so
wrong. There is no bad music.

85
00:04:05,520 --> 00:04:08,880
If it's an orchestra, or a band, or
the wind in the trees,

86
00:04:08,880 --> 00:04:12,120
or your next-door neighbour singing
in the shower, music is beautiful,

87
00:04:12,120 --> 00:04:14,720
and the God of Music has no power
over you,

88
00:04:14,720 --> 00:04:18,160
because music belongs to everyone.
The amazing human race -

89
00:04:18,160 --> 00:04:22,440
sailing through the cosmos and
singing to the stars. Forever.

90
00:04:23,840 --> 00:04:25,160
Love you. Bye-bye.

91
00:04:25,160 --> 00:04:26,480
CHEERING AND APPLAUSE

92
00:04:26,480 --> 00:04:28,360
VWORP!

